  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>You know the @UUID[Compendium.materia-dnd.spells.Item.matSplShockingGr]{Shocking Grasp} cantrip. You can cast it as normal, and you can also cast it as a bonus action a number of times equal to your proficiency bonus, regaining all expended uses when you finish a long rest.</p><p>Starting at 3rd level, you can cast the @UUID[Compendium.materia-dnd.spells.Item.matSplFeatherFal]{Feather Fall} spell with this trait. Starting at 5th level, you can also cast the @UUID[Compendium.materia-dnd.spells.Item.matSplLevitate00]{Levitate} spell with this trait. Once you cast feather fall or levitate with this trait, you cannot cast that spell with it again until you finish a long rest. You can also cast either of those spells using any spell slots you have of the appropriate level.</p><p>Intelligence, Wisdom, or Charisma is your spellcasting ability for these spells when you cast them with this trait (choose when you select this species). None of these spells require spell components when you cast them with this trait.</p>",
